Thief Nora: There's a strange switch here!
Mage Relm: There are traps in ruins like this, you know.

Mage Relm: This is definitely... not the time to be
explaining, right!?

Royal Court Official Emoni: This is a special structure.
Would you mind getting off once?

Royal Court Official Emoni: There should be a similar
structure on the upper floor as well...
Mage Relm: Oh, um, it doesn't react even when I get on.

Royal Court Official Emoni: It is likely that a certain
amount of weight is required. However, the same conditions
may not apply to the upper floor.

Priestess Sophia: I see... So this place is the Tower of
Betrayal, huh?

Priestess Sophia: In order to go upstairs, someone needs to
be on the lower floor. If the person on the lower floor
betrays us, the people on the upper floor will be unable to
escape.

Clea: In that case, it's okay. None of us will betray each
other.

Priestess Sophia: I like that about you, Clea-chan, but
this person might betray us.

Royal Court Official Emoni: T-That's not true! I am here
under the orders of the royal court!

Clea: From what I can see from the outside, there should be
three people needed on the top floor.
Clea: Emoni-san and I will go to the top floor.

Priestess Sophia: I will follow Clea-chan, but please be
careful, okay?
